Program: Outlook
Title: 16/07/2012
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00vc0g4
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 17 Jul 2012
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, Matthew Bannister meets the man who brought down one of Colombia's most powerful drug cartels - and now lives in secret in the US; the photographer who captures every volcanic eruption in Iceland and takes huge personal risks to get a great picture; and the Jamaican man living in London tells us why his vegetable patch reminds him of his roots. Photographer Ragnar Th. Sigurdsson's book is called Magma: Icelandic Volcanoes. Show less